			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	EdTech StartUp Hiring Sales Director in Cambridge, MA</p>
<p>
	Over the past four years, BetterLesson has developed the best-in-class social curriculum sharing site for teachers. We build custom solutions for states and districts that allow access to incredibly high-quality, teacher-created lessons and common core aligned curricula. We are a rapidly-growing site with over 90,000 current members, over 100,000 teacher-created lessons, and over 350,000 resources.</p>
<p>
	We are looking for a highly-motivated, self-directed team member to lead our sales operation from our Cambridge, MA office. Ideal candidate has experience with direct sales to schools, districts, and states. Experience selling the Software as a Service (SAAS) model and knowledge of the current Ed Policy landscape are a definite plus.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities:<br />
	- Building relationships with a variety of existing accounts<br />
	- Calling and emailing administrators to facilitate deal closure<br />
	- Managing the sales-cycle, including contract generation and other deliverables for closing<br />
	- Meeting monthly sales goals&nbsp;<br />
	- Understanding an account&rsquo;s needs and effectively communicating how we will meet those needs&nbsp;<br />
	- Rapidly learning online BetterLesson&#39;s product offering<br />
	- Using SalesForce.com for lead management and sales forecasting<br />
	- Ensuring 100% satisfaction with all customers<br />
	- Prioritizing opportunities and applying appropriate resources</p>
<p>
	<br />
	Qualifications:<br />
	- 4-year degree required<br />
	- Obvious passion and people skills<br />
	- 4+ years successful sales experience, SaaS or education experience preferred<br />
	- Consistent over-achievement in past experiences<br />
	- Technically adept, experienced with web technologies</p>
<br />
<p>
	Benefits:<br />
	- Competitive salary with uncapped commission<br />
	- Subsidized medical coverage<br />
	- 15 days of vacation (plus your birthday off!)<br />
	- Lots of snacks and drinks<br />
	- Casual dress environment</p>
